        <span class="property-type">Dictionary&lt;string, Immutable<wbr>Array&lt;string&gt;&gt;</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>IP restriction rule headers.
X-Forwarded-Host (https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/X-Forwarded-Host#Examples).
The matching logic is ..</p>
<ul>
<li>If the property is null or empty (default), all hosts(or lack of) are allowed.</li>
<li>A value is compared using ordinal-ignore-case (excluding port number).</li>
<li>Subdomain wildcards are permitted but don't match the root domain. For example, *.contoso.com matches the subdomain foo.contoso.com
but not the root domain contoso.com or multi-level foo.bar.contoso.com</li>
<li>Unicode host names are allowed but are converted to Punycode for matching.</li>
</ul>
<p>X-Forwarded-For (https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/X-Forwarded-For#Examples).
The matching logic is ..</p>
<ul>
<li>If the property is null or empty (default), any forwarded-for chains (or lack of) are allowed.</li>
<li>If any address (excluding port number) in the chain (comma separated) matches the CIDR defined by the property.</li>
</ul>
<p>X-Azure-FDID and X-FD-HealthProbe.
The matching logic is exact match.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="ipaddress_csharp">

but not the root domain contoso.com or multi-level foo.bar.contoso.com</li>
<li>Unicode host names are allowed but are converted to Punycode for matching.</li>
</ul>
<p>X-Forwarded-For (https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/X-Forwarded-For#Examples).
The matching logic is ..</p>
<ul>
<li>If the property is null or empty (default), any forwarded-for chains (or lack of) are allowed.</li>
<li>If any address (excluding port number) in the chain (comma separated) matches the CIDR defined by the property.</li>
</ul>
<p>X-Azure-FDID and X-FD-HealthProbe.
The matching logic is exact match.</p>

but not the root domain contoso.com or multi-level foo.bar.contoso.com</li>
<li>Unicode host names are allowed but are converted to Punycode for matching.</li>

<li>If any address (excluding port number) in the chain (comma separated) matches the CIDR defined by the property.</li>
